# Graph Neural Network (GCN) on MNIST

This project implements a Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) using PyTorch Geometric for digit classification on the MNIST dataset.

Each image is converted into a graph where:

* Nodes represent pixels
* Node features include pixel intensity along with normalized spatial coordinates (x, y)
* Edges connect neighboring pixels to preserve spatial structure

The model consists of multiple GCN layers followed by global mean pooling and a fully connected layer for classification.

## Results

The model achieves an accuracy of approximately **80%** on the test dataset.

## Key Idea

By incorporating spatial (x, y) information along with intensity, the model captures both structural and feature-based relationships in the image, making it suitable for graph-based learning.
